HEADWORD: Yucca borer
<hw>Yuc"ca bor`er</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A California boring weevil
(<spn>Yuccaborus frontalis</spn>).</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A large
mothlike butterfly (<spn>Megathymus yuccae</spn>) of the family
<fam>Megatimidae</fam>, whose larva bores in yucca roots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

